    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Megalink Traffic Rotator Overview &amp; Pricing</h2>
      <p>Megalink Traffic Rotator is one of several paid upgrades within the OLSP system built and operated by Wayne Crowe Limited, a UK-registered company. It sits above the free Mega Link entry point and below higher-tier upgrades such as Team Builders, functioning as a recurring traffic add-on for members who want to automate visitor flow to their funnel without managing traffic campaigns themselves.</p>

      <h3>What's Included</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Monthly traffic allocation:</strong> OLSP sets aside a reserved pool of traffic from its wider solo ad operation and distributes a share to each rotator subscriber's Magick or Mega Link on a recurring monthly basis.</li>
        <li><strong>OLSP-native rotation:</strong> The member's Magick/Mega Link is placed into OLSP's internal rotator; no external rotator account or tracking tool is required.</li>
        <li><strong>Traffic distribution across Megalink destinations (rotator function):</strong> For users with multiple Megalink variations, the service can distribute incoming traffic across different destinations to facilitate A/B testing of landing pages, hooks, and campaign angles — according to independent analysis, not official vendor documentation.</li>
        <li><strong>Hands-off management:</strong> OLSP's team handles traffic generation and routing; no active campaign management is required from the subscriber after initial setup.</li>
        <li><strong>Cancellable subscription:</strong> The service is described on the official products page as a monthly subscription with no stated minimum term.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Reported Pricing</h3>
      <div class="callout warn">
        <strong>Pricing note:</strong> The $47/month figure is confirmed on two separate official OLSP pages — the products and descriptions page and the Traffic Rotator sales page — making it one of the more reliably documented prices in the OLSP ecosystem. However, OLSP products and pricing can change. The sales page presents the $47 as a permanent discount from $100; treat that framing as marketing copy rather than a confirmed retail price. Verify the current price directly on the official page before subscribing.
      </div>
