      <h3>4.2 Key Performance Categories</h3>

      <h4>Traffic Quality and Volume</h4>
      <p>The official sales page describes the traffic as coming from OLSP's "secret source of high-quality traffic" and frames the monthly allocation as "$100 worth" of visitors. Neither claim is independently verified. No public technical documentation describes the traffic source in detail — whether it is solo ad list traffic, paid display traffic, or some other origin — and no independent conversion rate audit exists. The characterisation of this traffic as "Tier 1" or "high-quality" is vendor language, not a verified specification.</p>

      <h4>Split-Testing Utility</h4>
      <p>Independent analysts — not official vendor materials — identify split-testing across multiple Megalink destinations as the strongest genuine use case for this service. According to one independent review, the rotator can distribute traffic across different Megalink landing page variants and track per-destination performance, enabling comparisons of hooks, bridge pages, and offer angles. This is a meaningful capability for an affiliate who is already generating enough OLSP income to justify systematic optimisation. It is not a beginner use case.</p>

      <h4>"Guaranteed Commissions" Claim</h4>
      <div class="callout warn">
        <strong>This claim requires careful reading:</strong> The official sales page states that the Traffic Rotator provides "100% guaranteed commissions" and describes it as a "100% autopilot commission generating program." These phrases appear to mean that OLSP pays a commission on every visitor routed through the Magick Link — not that the subscriber is guaranteed a specific income or a profitable return. No independent verification of this claim exists, and the sales page provides no commission rate, no earnings disclosure, and no data on typical subscriber outcomes. Treat all income-adjacent language on the sales page as vendor marketing copy, not a contractual earnings guarantee.
      </div>

      <h4>Community and Support</h4>
      <p>There is no dedicated support channel documented for the Traffic Rotator specifically. Support appears to operate through the broader OLSP community — a Facebook group where setup guides and optimisation tips are shared by members — and through OLSP's general training resources. No standalone technical manual, FAQ, or help-desk process for the rotator was found in publicly available material.</p>
